headline: Is Rivian Stock Fairly Priced After Amazon Tests GM BrightDrop Electric Vans?
summary: Deciding what to do with your Rivian Automotive stock right now might feel like you are straddling the line between fear of missing out and lingering market skepticism. Over the past month, Rivian’s share price has jumped 9.6%, only to slip by 5.3% in the last week. Even on a bigger timescale, there is a tale of two charts here: a modest 1.6% gain year-to-date contrasts sharply with a staggering 65.7% drop over the past three years.
